<p>It's not the smoothest gameplay, but being my first game, I was just thrilled to get the damn thing to work.  I must have spent at least an hour trying to keep the player from falling through the floor, which was quite the opposite of the tranquil experience I was going for.  There's not much else to this game.  I was just learning the basics, and in the process I wanted to see if I could make a virtual space that made me happy.  A serene hallway with some big windows looking out into an endless artificial heaven with a few pictures from our Ireland trip hastily pasted to the walls.</p>

<h2>Beach</h2>

