<p>Does this one feel a little smoother?  I studied up on ways to make the player movements feel more natural.  Fine tuned sensitivity, a subtle headbob when you move, and FOOTSTEPS.  What a difference sound makes to giving the player a sense of comfort.  The free wave audio I found is so good, it almost makes you forget that there isn't any water in sight.  I also added a seagull.  On a random interval, this invisible bird will pick a spot above your head and play a hidden audio track to make you feel like he is circling freely in the sky.  Also, there is a hidden message in this game - were you able to find it?</p>
